## 1. Interface Layout

Your app has **5 major sections**:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  File Menu Bar                                                       │
├──────────┬────────────┬────────────┬────────────┬──────────────────┤
│          │            │            │            │                  │
│  LEFT    │  ORIGINAL  │ PROCESSED  │ RECON-     │  RIGHT           │
│  SIDEBAR │  IMAGE     │ IMAGE      │ STRUCTED   │  SIDEBAR         │
│          │  PANEL     │ PANEL      │ PANEL      │                  │
│ Filters  │            │            │            │  Compression     │
│ Geometry │            │            │            │  Statistics      │
│ Compress │            │            │            │                  │
│          │            │            │            │                  │
├──────────┴────────────┴────────────┴────────────┴──────────────────┤
│  Status Bar                                                          │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### 1.1 File Menu (Top-Left)
| Action | What it does |
|--------|-------------|
| **Open Image** (Ctrl+O) | Opens a `.ppm` P6 file → loads into `Matrix<Pixel>` → displays in Original panel |
| **Save Processed** (Ctrl+S) | Saves the processed image back as `.ppm` P6 |
| **Exit** | Closes the application |

### 1.2 Left Sidebar — Operation Controls

#### FILTERS Section
| Button | What happens behind the scenes |
|--------|-------------------------------|
| **Grayscale Conversion** | Calls `ImageProcessor::toGrayscale()` → applies BT.601 formula: `gray = 0.299·R + 0.587·G + 0.114·B` to every pixel in the Matrix → result shown in Processed panel |
| **Sobel Edge Detection** | Calls `ImageProcessor::sobelEdgeDetect()` → creates two `Matrix<int>` 3×3 kernels (Gx, Gy) → convolves over every pixel → computes gradient magnitude `√(Gx² + Gy²)` → result shown in Processed panel |

#### GEOMETRY Section
| Control | What it does |
|---------|-------------|
| **Scale Dropdown** (50%, 100%, 200%) | Select scaling factor |
| **Scale Button** | Calls `ImageProcessor::scale()` → uses nearest-neighbor interpolation → creates new `Matrix<Pixel>` at new dimensions → shown in Processed panel |

#### COMPRESSION Section
| Button | What happens |
|--------|-------------|
| **Huffman Compress** | Takes processed image (or original if no filter applied) → serializes `Matrix<Pixel>` to byte array → builds frequency table → builds Huffman tree using MinHeap → generates codes → encodes to bitstream → writes `.huf` file → updates stats |
| **Huffman Decompress** | Reads `.huf` file → rebuilds tree from stored frequencies → decodes bitstream → reconstructs `Matrix<Pixel>` → shown in Reconstructed panel |

### 1.3 Three Image Panels (Center)

| Panel | Purpose | When it updates |
|-------|---------|----------------|
| **ORIGINAL** | Shows the raw loaded image | When you open a `.ppm` file |
| **PROCESSED** | Shows the result after applying a filter/scale | After clicking Grayscale, Sobel, or Scale |
| **RECONSTRUCTED** | Shows the decompressed image | After clicking Huffman Decompress |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The Reconstructed image should be **pixel-identical** to the source that was compressed, because Huffman coding is **lossless**. This is a key viva point!

### 1.4 Right Sidebar — Compression Statistics

| Field | What it shows |
|-------|---------------|
| **Original** | Raw data size = `width × height × 3` bytes (3 bytes per pixel: R, G, B) |
| **Compressed** | Size of the `.huf` file on disk |
| **Compression Rate** | `(1 - compressed/original) × 100%` — must be ≥ 30% |
| **Progress Bar** | Visual representation of the compression rate |

### 1.5 Status Bar (Bottom)
Shows contextual messages like "Image loaded successfully", "Huffman compression complete", etc.

