## 2. Complete Workflow

### Step-by-step: Load → Process → Compress → Decompress

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["📁 Open .ppm file"] --> B["Image::load() reads P6 header + RGB bytes"]
    B --> C["Pixels stored in Matrix<Pixel> (heap-allocated)"]
    C --> D["Displayed in ORIGINAL panel"]
    D --> E{"Apply filter?"}
    E -->|Grayscale| F["BT.601 formula on each pixel"]
    E -->|Sobel| G["3×3 convolution with Matrix<int> kernels"]
    E -->|Scale| H["Nearest-neighbor resampling"]
    F --> I["Result in PROCESSED panel"]
    G --> I
    H --> I
    I --> J["Click Huffman Compress"]
    J --> K["Serialize Matrix<Pixel> → byte array"]
    K --> L["Count byte frequencies (0-255)"]
    L --> M["Build MinHeap with frequency nodes"]
    M --> N["Extract 2 mins, merge, insert → repeat"]
    N --> O["Huffman tree built"]
    O --> P["DFS to generate bit codes per byte"]
    P --> Q["Encode bytes → compressed bitstream"]
    Q --> R["Write .huf file"]
    R --> S["Stats updated in RIGHT sidebar"]
    S --> T["Click Huffman Decompress"]
    T --> U["Read .huf → rebuild tree from frequencies"]
    U --> V["Decode bitstream → byte array"]
    V --> W["Reconstruct Matrix<Pixel>"]
    W --> X["Displayed in RECONSTRUCTED panel"]
```

