## 4. DSA Concepts Used

| Concept | Where in Project | Complexity |
|---------|-----------------|-----------|
| **Templates** | `Matrix<T>` — works with `Pixel`, `int`, any type | — |
| **Dynamic Memory** (`new`/`delete`) | Matrix rows, Image pixels pointer, Heap array, Huffman nodes, raw/compressed arrays | — |
| **Rule of Three** | Matrix (copy ctor, operator=, destructor), Image (same) | — |
| **Binary Tree** | Huffman tree (HuffmanNode with left/right children) | — |
| **Min-Heap** (Priority Queue) | MinHeap class for building Huffman tree | Insert: O(log n), Extract: O(log n) |
| **Greedy Algorithm** | Huffman coding — always merge two least-frequent | Optimal prefix code |
| **2D Convolution** | Sobel edge detection with 3×3 kernels | O(W × H) |
| **Bit Manipulation** | Encoding bytes to bitstream, decoding bits from bytes | O(1) per bit |
| **Binary File I/O** | PPM P6 read/write, .huf read/write | O(n) |

